@node a "What is FileShield"

  FileShield is small freeware utility to protect Your
  executable files against lot of @{"link-viruses" link j}.

  This program is designed for advanced people,
  so be carefull!

  Because program @{b}modifies@{ub} executable files,
  You using this program for Your own risk!

  I @{b}take no@{ub} any responsibility for any damages/losses
  done with this program!

  Source code in assembler (because its dangerous) is
  only buyable (10USD), and Your address will be stored
  in my database.
@endnode
@node b "Requirements"

   You need: 2.0 operating system or newer,
             asl.library & gadtools.library.

   To localization You need also locale.library (OS2.1+).

   @{b}The modified files need OS2.0 too!@{ub}
@endnode
@node c "Gadgets"

   @{b}About@{ub} - informations :-)
   Available also from underlined character key and from Help key

   @{b}Modify file@{ub} - do as name
   Available also from underlined character key
   After choose of file there are two possibilities:
    - if success - will be created backup copy of `clean` file
    - if not, You got an error message, and file will not
      be changed
    - if file is already protected by FS (new or old)
      You will be able to clean file.

   To quit You can press close gadget or hit ESC on keyboard.
@endnode
@node d "How it works"

   Program adds special @{"hunk" link i} to executable files, which contains
   no special commands replaced by @{"first hunk increasers" link k},
   and uses Reloc32Short @{"hunk" link i} unknown for some @{"hunk adders" link l}.

   The protected files are known by LoadSeg from OS2.0 or better,
   so @{b}DON`T FORGET!@{ub}
   
   Program know only some @{"hunks" link i} and @{b}can`t@{ub} protect some
   files with special @{"hunks" link i} like for example DPaint.

   @{b}Practically protects Your executables against 95% of popular file
   @{"linking viruses" link j}.@{ub}
@endnode
@node e "What it gives"

   Files protected by FileShield v1.2+ becomes uninfectable by
   very big part of@{"linking viruses" link j}
   and thats all!

   If You have files protected by old FileShield better unlink
   old ones and protect again.
@endnode
